    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="effective-date">
            Last updated: July 19, 2025
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>This Privacy Policy ("Policy") describes how <strong>Shrey Bot</strong> (the "Bot", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, processes, stores, and protects your personal information when you use our Discord bot services.</p>
            
            <p>By using Shrey Bot, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described herein.</p>

            <div class="important">
                <strong>Important:</strong> This Privacy Policy complies with applicable data protection laws including GDPR, India's Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023, and Discord's Developer Policy.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Data Controller Information</h2>
            <p>The data controller for your personal information is the operator of Shrey Bot:</p>
            
            <div class="contact-info">
                <p><strong>Location:</strong> New Delhi, Delhi, India</p>
                <p><strong>Governing Law:</strong> Laws of India</p>
                <p><strong>Contact:</strong> Available through appropriate Discord channels</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect and process the following categories of personal data to provide our bot services:</p>
            
            <div class="data-types">
                <h3>Automatically Collected Data:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Discord User ID:</strong> Your unique Discord identifier for command processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Discord Username:</strong> Your current Discord display name and tag</li>
                    <li><strong>Server Information:</strong> Discord server ID, name, and channel information where the bot operates</li>
                    <li><strong>Message Data:</strong> Content of messages when directly interacting with the bot</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Commands used, timestamps, and interaction patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Error logs, performance metrics, and system information</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Data We Do NOT Collect:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Private messages not directed to the bot</li>
                    <li>Voice chat recordings</li>
                    <li>Email addresses or phone numbers</li>
                    <li>Payment or financial information</li>
                    <li>Files or attachments not sent to the bot</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
            <p>We process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:</p>
            
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Data Type</th>
                    <th>Legal Basis</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>User IDs & Commands</td>
                    <td>Legitimate Interest</td>
                    <td>Providing bot functionality and services</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Server Data</td>
                    <td>Contract Performance</td>
                    <td>Operating within Discord servers</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Usage Analytics</td>
                    <td>Legitimate Interest</td>
                    <td>Improving bot performance and features</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Error Logs</td>
                    <td>Legitimate Interest</td>
                    <td>Debugging and system maintenance</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>5. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Service Provision:</strong> To operate the bot and provide requested functionality</li>
                <li><strong>Command Processing:</strong> To understand and respond to user commands</li>
                <li><strong>Performance Monitoring:</strong> To ensure the bot operates efficiently and reliably</li>
                <li><strong>Security:</strong> To protect against abuse, spam, and unauthorized access</li>
                <li><strong>Improvement:</strong> To analyze usage patterns and enhance bot features</li>
                <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> To meet legal obligations and Discord's policies</li>
                <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to user inquiries and provide support</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>6. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your data only in the following circumstances:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Discord Platform:</strong> Data shared through normal Discord API interactions</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or governmental authority</li>
                <li><strong>Safety:</strong> To protect the safety of users, the public, or our services</li>
                <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> With trusted partners who assist in operating our services (under strict confidentiality agreements)</li>
                <li><strong>Business Transfer:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="important">
                <strong>Data Transfers:</strong> Your data may be processed outside your country of residence. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place for international transfers as required by applicable law.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy:</p>
            
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Data Type</th>
                    <th>Retention Period</th>
                    <th>Reason</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Command History</td>
                    <td>30 days</td>
                    <td>Debugging and support purposes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Error Logs</td>
                    <td>90 days</td>
                    <td>Technical troubleshooting</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>User Preferences</td>
                    <td>Until bot removal or user request</td>
                    <td>Maintaining user settings</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Analytics Data</td>
                    <td>12 months (anonymized)</td>
                    <td>Service improvement</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Safety Logs</td>
                    <td>2 years</td>
                    <td>Security and abuse prevention</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <p>When the bot is removed from a server, all associated data is automatically deleted within 7 days unless retention is required for legal compliance or safety purposes[25].</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>8. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
            <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
            
            <div class="legal-basis">
                <h3>General Rights:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> Request copies of your personal data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> Request limitation of data processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a portable format</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to certain types of processing</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Additional Rights (EU/UK Users under GDPR):</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right to Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent for processing at any time</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Lodge a Complaint:</strong> File complaints with data protection authorities</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Automated Decision Making:</strong> Protection against automated decision making</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Indian Users (under DPDPA 2023):</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right to Confirmation:</strong> Confirm whether personal data is being processed</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Nomination:</strong> Nominate someone to exercise rights in case of death or incapacity</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Grievance Redressal:</strong> Access to grievance mechanisms</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us through appropriate Discord channels or community forums.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Shrey Bot complies with children's privacy protection requirements:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>The bot follows Discord's minimum age requirements (13+ in most jurisdictions)</li>
                <li>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13</li>
                <li>Enhanced protection measures apply to users identified as minors</li>
                <li>Parents/guardians can request deletion of their child's data</li>
                <li>We comply with applicable child protection laws including COPPA and GDPR provisions for children</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="important">
                <strong>Note:</strong> If you become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately so we can delete such information.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data transmission and storage encryption</li>
                <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Restricted access to personal data on a need-to-know basis</li>
                <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Periodic security assessments and updates</li>
                <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> Collection and processing of only necessary data</li>
                <li><strong>Secure Infrastructure:</strong> Industry-standard security practices</li>
                <li><strong>Incident Response:</strong> Procedures for handling data breaches</li>
            </ul>

            <p>However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>11. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
            <p>Shrey Bot does not use cookies or web tracking technologies. However, Discord itself may use cookies and tracking mechanisms in accordance with their own Privacy Policy[1].</p>
            
            <p>Our bot only processes data necessary for its functionality within the Discord platform.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>12. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>Shrey Bot integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Discord API:</strong> For all bot interactions and functionality</li>
                <li><strong>Hosting Services:</strong> For bot infrastructure (with appropriate data protection agreements)</li>
            </ul>

            <p>These services have their own privacy policies, and we recommend reviewing them. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party services.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>13. Cross-Border Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. When we transfer data internationally, we ensure:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Appropriate safeguards are in place as required by applicable law</li>
                <li>Data protection standards are maintained</li>
                <li>Compliance with applicable cross-border transfer regulations</li>
                <li>Use of standard contractual clauses where required</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>14. Data Breach Notification</h2>
            <p>In the event of a data breach that poses risks to your rights and freedoms, we will:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Notify relevant data protection authorities within 72 hours (where required by law)</li>
                <li>Inform affected users without undue delay</li>
                <li>Provide clear information about the breach and steps being taken</li>
                <li>Offer guidance on protective measures users can take</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>15. Automated Decision Making</h2>
            <p>Shrey Bot may use automated processing for:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Spam detection and prevention</li>
                <li>Command processing and responses</li>
                <li>Basic content moderation</li>
            </ul>

            <p>You have the right to object to automated decision-making and request human intervention where such decisions significantly affect you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>16. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>The updated policy will be posted with a new "Last updated" date</li>
                <li>Significant changes will be communicated through appropriate channels</li>
                <li>Continued use of the bot after changes constitutes acceptance</li>
                <li>For material changes affecting GDPR rights, we will seek renewed consent where required</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>17. Compliance and Regulatory Framework</h2>
            <p>This Privacy Policy is designed to comply with:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><strong>EU GDPR</strong> (General Data Protection Regulation)</li>
                <li><strong>UK GDPR</strong> and Data Protection Act 2018</li>
                <li><strong>India DPDPA 2023</strong> (Digital Personal Data Protection Act)</li>
                <li><strong>Discord Developer Policy</strong> and Terms of Service</li>
                <li><strong>COPPA</strong> (Children's Online Privacy Protection Act)</li>
                <li>Other applicable local data protection laws</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>18. Grievance Redressal</h2>
            <p>For users in India, as per DPDPA 2023 requirements:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>We provide mechanisms for grievance redressal</li>
                <li>Complaints will be acknowledged and addressed promptly</li>
                <li>Users can escalate unresolved issues to the Data Protection Authority</li>
                <li>Contact information for grievances is provided in the contact section below</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-info">
            <h2>19. Contact Information</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:</p>
            
            <p><strong>For General Inquiries:</strong> Through appropriate Discord channels or community forums</p>
            <p><strong>For Data Protection Requests:</strong> Please clearly indicate "Privacy Request" in your communication</p>
            <p><strong>For Indian Users (DPDPA Grievances):</strong> Indicate "DPDPA Grievance" in your communication</p>
            
            <div class="important">
                <strong>Response Time:</strong> We aim to respond to all privacy-related inquiries within 30 days, or as required by applicable law.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>20. Effective Date and Acknowledgment</h2>
            <p>This Privacy Policy is effective as of July 19, 2025, and applies to all users of Shrey Bot.</p>
            
            <p><strong>By using Shrey Bot, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy.</strong></p>
        </div>
